caption: Went here with a buddy last Friday- we arrived around 3:30pm so not busy at all. Service was lackluster and I felt like I had to wave the waiter down each time for service. For the price and the fact that it’s cash only I didn’t feel like it was worth it. We ordered 4 mezcal drinks and food.

Regardless, the point is tacos, and those are delicious. However, honestly you can get the same tacos from the taco truck a few blocks over. Taste and look the same. Same price as the truck too! And the truck folks aren’t weird either hah. That’s why I’m giving 3 stars - Not special, but they have tacos.

Went here with a friend - we ordered 4 shots of mezcal and paid the $63 bill with cash. I was feeling generous and left all the change (waiter asked me if I wanted change). I got home and noticed that a 20% gratuity had been added to the bill, meaning I had tipped him more than 50% for doing practically nothing. Outrageous that he had the nerve to ask me if I needed change knowing full well that the tip was included, which is to say nothing of obnoxiousness of a mandatory gratuity line item that could simply be included in the prices.

Between the cozy vibe and delicious Mexican food, it's hard not to want to love Cerveceria, but the only consistent thing about this restaurant is the abismal quality of service.  I even tolerate it and honestly eat here somewhat often, because the food is so good. You just have to know what you're getting into, which is the purpose of this review. Here are a few situations you might encounter:  1) Entering an 85% empty restaurant and told that all open tables are reserved. You are only given a seat when you tell the "host" you're just interested in a quick meal, and subsequently given a time limit for your meal.  2) Your server bring your entrées out 20 minutes apart from your guest. When you get their attention, the server lies and tells you that your single taco just "takes longer."  3) You ask for the check because the rest of your order still hasn't arrived an hour later and the server argues with you, does not apologize, or make eye contact.  4) The staff gives customers attitude, is unapproachable, aloof, or unfriendly.  Cerveceria is an amazing example of how NOT to run a service-oriented business, especially a restaurant. Advice to the owners. Hire entirely new service staff. But seriously the place is very charming and the Mexican food is some of the best in Williamsburg. Enjoy!
